    <body>
      <head>Smart Playlists</head>
      
      <p>These are unique phrases Iâ€™ve placed into the ID3 Comment tags of music 
        files. Creating smart playlists is then as easy as 
        <code>Comment contains PHRASE</code>.</p>
      <p>The smart playlist encompassing (most) all of my music uses these rules:
        <list>
          <item>Comment does not contain <q>NOPE</q></item>
          <item>Comment does not contain <q>Christmas</q></item>
        </list>
      </p>
      
      <div xml:id="pl-solutions">
        <head>Solutions to Needs</head>
        
        <list>
          <label>Awake the Day</label>
          <item>For starting the day.</item>
          
          <label>Complicated</label>
          <item>For getting through the day.</item>
          
          <label>The Drive!</label>
          <item>For long drives.</item>
          
          <label>Fun Times</label>
          <item>For dancing.</item>
          
          <label>The Girl in Byakkoya</label>
          <item>For keeping up energy while focusing on an activity.</item>
          
          <label>NOPE</label>
          <item>For not hearing this song ever again (for a while). The tag is 
            mostly used for suppressing songs on other smart playlists.</item>
          
          <label>Singable</label>
          <item>For singing.</item>
          
          <label>Sleepytimes</label>
          <item>For winding down the day.</item>
          
          <label>Whistle While You Work</label>
          <item>For cleaning.</item>
        </list>
      </div>
      
